terval\n2. **Per-story statuses** (`mapSprintStatuses`) — reads sprint-status.yaml, maps to `StoryStatusEntry[]`, fed to `rendererHandle.updateStories()` on startup and every 5s poll\n3. **Ralph message parsing** (`parseRalphMessage`) — parses `[SUCCESS]`, `[WARN]`, `[ERROR]` lines from stderr and calls `rendererHandle.addMessage()` with typed `StoryMessage` objects\n4. **DashboardFormatter removal** — confirmed not imported in run.ts, test verifies this\n5. **Helper extraction** — moved `countStories`, `buildSpawnArgs` to run-helpers.ts; run.ts re-exports for backward compatibility\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **run.ts at exactly 300 lines**: It was 358 originally and the story required staying under 300 (NFR9). Extracting `countStories` and `buildSpawnArgs` alongside the new helpers got it to exactly 300. Any future changes to run.ts will need to extract more.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors in test files**: The test mocking pattern uses loosely-typed `vi.fn()` calls that don't match the strict type signatures. These errors exist across many test files (bridge.test.ts, status.test.ts, etc.) — not introduced by this story.\n- **Coverage gap in polling interval**: The 5-second `setInterval` callback in run.ts (lines 207-228) is not directly tested because it requires timer manipulation. The helper functions it calls (`formatElapsed`, `mapSprintStatuses`) are tested independently with 100% coverage.\n- **run-helpers.test.ts at 303 lines**: Slightly over the 300-line NFR9 limit. Test files are typically exempt from this constraint but worth noting."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8c1969604e3b929a (use SendMessage with to: 'a8c1969604e3b929a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 120776\ntool_uses: 71\nduration_ms: 623527</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"64c1e9b9-a641-40be-ae67-07aee0c47965","uuid":"9ba80d56-b737-4aaa-99c3-547a9ed04ae6","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:13:26.053Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story 