{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y3K2KNYZh1pzvr6xrAes81","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# src/lib — Shared Libraries\n     2→\n     3→Pure library modules consumed by CLI commands (`src/commands/`) and by each other. No CLI entry points, no side effects on import.\n     4→\n     5→## State & Output\n     6→\n     7→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n     8→|------|---------|-------------|\n     9→| state.ts | YAML front-matter state persistence in `.claude/codeharness.local.md` | `readState`, `writeState`, `readStateWithBody`, `getStatePath`, `HarnessState` |\n    10→| output.ts | Structured `[OK]/[FAIL]/[WARN]/[INFO]` CLI output with JSON mode | `ok`, `fail`, `warn`, `info`, `jsonOutput` |\n    11→\n    12→## Stack & Environment\n    13→\n    14→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    15→|------|---------|-------------|\n    16→| stack-detect.ts | Detects project language (nodejs/python) and app type | `detectStack`, `detectAppType`, `AppType` |\n    17→| stack-path.ts | XDG-compliant paths for shared observability stack | `getStackDir`, `getComposeFilePath`, `ensureStackDir` |\n    18→| templates.ts | File generation with `{{var}}` mustache-style rendering | `generateFile`, `renderTemplate` |\n    19→\n    20→## Docker & Observability\n    21→\n    22→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    23→|------|---------|-------------|\n    24→| docker.ts | Docker Compose lifecycle — start/stop, health checks, remote probing | `startSharedStack`, `stopSharedStack`, `isStackRunning`, `getStackHealth`, `checkRemoteEndpoint` |\n    25→| otlp.ts | OTLP instrumentation — package install, script patching, env vars | `instrumentProject`, `configureOtlpEnvVars`, `patchNodeStartScript` |\n    26→\n    27→## Coverage & Testing\n    28→\n    29→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    30→|------|---------|-------------|\n    31→| coverage.ts | Coverage tool detection (Vitest/c8/coverage.py), execution, evaluation, per-file floors | `detectCoverageTool`, `runCoverage`, `checkOnlyCoverage`, `evaluateCoverage`, `checkPerFileCoverage`, `getTestCommand` |\n    32→\n    33→## Verification Pipeline\n    34→\n    35→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    36→|------|---------|-------------|\n    37→| verify-parser.ts | Parses story ACs with type classification (ui/api/db/general) | `parseStoryACs`, `classifyAC`, `ParsedAC` |\n    38→| verify.ts | Verification orchestrator — preconditions, proof quality validation, Showboat, state | `checkPreconditions`, `validateProofQuality`, `ProofQuality`, `createProofDocument`, `runShowboatVerify`, `closeBeadsIssue`, `proofHasContent` (deprecated) |\n    39→| verify-env.ts | Black-box verification environment — Docker image build (npm pack/pip install), clean workspace prep, env check, cleanup | `buildVerifyImage`, `prepareVerifyWorkspace`, `checkVerifyEnv`, `cleanupVerifyEnv`, `computeDistHash`, `isValidStoryKey` |\n    40→| verifier-session.ts | Black-box verifier session spawner — runs `claude --print` in clean workspace, returns `Result<VerifyResult>`, copies proof back to project | `spawnVerifierSession`, `copyProofToProject` |\n    41→\n    42→## Documentation Health\n    43→\n    44→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    45→|------|---------|-------------|\n    46→| doc-health.ts | AGENTS.md/exec-plan freshness scanner, exec-plan lifecycle | `scanDocHealth`, `findModules`, `isDocStale`, `createExecPlan`, `completeExecPlan` |\n    47→\n    48→## Retrospective Parsing\n    49→\n    50→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    51→|------|---------|-------------|\n    52→| retro-parser.ts | Retro markdown parser — action item extraction, classification, priority derivation | `parseRetroActionItems`, `classifyFinding`, `derivePriority`, `RetroActionItem`, `Classification` |\n    53→\n    54→## GitHub CLI Integration\n    55→\n    56→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    57→|------|---------|-------------|\n    58→| github.ts | `gh` CLI wrapper — issue create/search, label management, repo detection, dedup | `isGhAvailable`, `ghIssueCreate`, `ghIssueSearch`, `findExistingGhIssue`, `getRepoFromRemote`, `parseRepoFromUrl`, `ensureLabels`, `GitHubError`, `GhIssue`, `RetroIssueTarget` |\n    59→\n    60→## Beads Integration (Issue Tracking)\n    61→\n    62→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    63→|------|---------|-------------|\n    64→| beads.ts | `bd` CLI wrapper — CRUD, init, hook detection, gap-id dedup | `createIssue`, `closeIssue`, `buildGapId`, `createOrFindIssue`, `BeadsError` |\n    65→| beads-sync.ts | Bidirectional sync between beads issues, story files, sprint YAML | `syncAll`, `readSprintStatus`, `updateSprintStatus` |\n    66→\n    67→## BMAD Method Integration\n    68→\n    69→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    70→|------|---------|-------------|\n    71→| bmad.ts | BMAD install, version detect, workflow patching (6 patches incl. `sprint-retro`), epics parser | `installBmad`, `applyAllPatches`, `parseEpicsFile`, `importStoriesToBeads`, `PATCH_TARGETS` (6 entries incl. `sprint-retro`) |\n    72→| patch-engine.ts | Marker-based idempotent patching for markdown/text files | `applyPatch`, `removePatch`, `hasPatch` |\n    73→\n    74→## Codebase Scanning & Onboarding\n    75→\n    76→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    77→|------|---------|-------------|\n    78→| scanner.ts | Module detection, source/test counting, coverage gap analysis, doc audit | `scanCodebase`, `analyzeCoverageGaps`, `auditDocumentation` |\n    79→| scan-cache.ts | Scan result cache in `.harness/last-onboard-scan.json` with 24h TTL | `saveScanCache`, `loadValidCache` |\n    80→| epic-generator.ts | Generates onboarding epic from scan findings, imports to beads | `generateOnboardingEpic`, `writeOnboardingEpic`, `formatEpicSummary`, `promptApproval`, `importOnboardingEpic` |\n    81→| onboard-checks.ts | Precondition checks and gap filtering for onboarding | `runPreconditions`, `findVerificationGaps`, `findPerFileCoverageGaps`, `findObservabilityGaps`, `getOnboardingProgress`, `filterTrackedGaps` |\n    82→\n    83→## Retry State Management\n    84→\n    85→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    86→|------|---------|-------------|\n    87→| retry-state.ts | Persistent story retry counters and flagged-story tracking in `ralph/.story_retries` and `ralph/.flagged_stories` | `readRetries`, `writeRetries`, `getRetryCount`, `setRetryCount`, `resetRetry`, `readFlaggedStories`, `writeFlaggedStories`, `removeFlaggedStory` |\n    88→\n    89→## Stream Parsing & Ink Rendering\n    90→\n    91→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    92→|------|---------|-------------|\n    93→| stream-parser.ts | Stateless NDJSON stream parser — converts Claude API streaming events into typed `StreamEvent` objects | `parseStreamLine`, `StreamEvent`, `StreamEventType` |\n    94→| ink-components.tsx | Ink/React terminal UI components — Header, ActiveTool, CompletedTool, LastThought, RetryNotice, StoryBreakdown, StoryMessages, App | `Header`, `App`, `SprintInfo`, `StoryStatusEntry`, `StoryStatusValue`, `StoryMessage` |\n    95→| ink-renderer.tsx | Ink renderer controller — creates/manages Ink instance, exposes RendererHandle for state updates, signal cleanup | `startRenderer`, `RendererHandle`, `RendererState`, `noopHandle` |\n    96→\n    97→## Dashboard Formatting\n    98→\n    99→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n   100→|------|---------|-------------|\n   101→| dashboard-formatter.ts | Parses ralph's structured output lines and reformats them as a clean dashboard with icons and progress tracking | `DashboardFormatter`, `formatDashboardLine` |\n   102→\n   103→## Dependency Management\n   104→\n   105→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n   106→|------|---------|-------------|\n   107→| deps.ts | Auto-install external tools (Showboat, beads) with fallback chains | `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY`, `installAllDependencies`, `CriticalDependencyError` |\n   108→\n   109→**Total: 29 library files across 13 categories.**\n   110→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XRogrW